* Most Important Core Rules
  * All descriptions, comments, and messages must be written in English

* README Writing Rules
  * Always in English
  * Overview and Tutorial should be at the front
  * License content should be at the end
  * Do not automatically add detailed content, only add prompts asking me to add it
    * If content is mentioned as core in requirements, add a recommendation that it is core content and should be added

* Commit Message Rules (CRITICAL - STRICTLY ENFORCED)
  * REQUIRED FORMAT (NO EXCEPTIONS):
  *   Line 1: Brief summary in imperative mood (MAX 50 characters)
  *   Line 2: Empty line
  *   Line 3+: Bullet points with "- " prefix
  * 
  * FORBIDDEN:
  *   - DO NOT write paragraphs or prose
  *   - DO NOT write "This commit...", "We updated...", "The changes include..."
  *   - DO NOT exceed 50 characters on first line
  * 
  * REQUIRED:
  *   - ALWAYS use imperative mood: "Add", "Fix", "Update", "Remove"
  *   - ALWAYS use bullet point format
  *   - ALWAYS write in English
  * 
  * Example (CORRECT FORMAT):
  * Refactor deployment scripts
  * 
  * - Translate Python scripts to English
  * - Update backend models
  * - Improve error handling 
